The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Oct. 4: Suzlon Energy Ltd has fixed an issue price of Rs 510 for its initial public offering of 2.93 crore shares. The issue, which has a price band of Rs 425-510, was oversubscribed 46 times, company sources said. The retail portion was oversubscribed 6.36 times.

 New Delhi, Oct. 4: Anil Nanda has asked the government to probe how Escorts Heart Institute and Research Centre, controlled by his elder brother, Rajan Nanda, was converted into a company from a charitable trust before being sold to Fortis Health Care. 

 New Delhi, Oct. 4: Jet Airways has announced a ?companion free? offer on its Delhi-London route, which will be valid for return tickets in the sector in November. Return air fare for two passengers in the economy class will be Rs 28,500 and in the business class Rs 1,86,020.

 New Delhi, Oct. 4: The government has not yet firmed up views on the J.J. Irani committee recommendations for amending the Companies Act, 1956, company affairs minister Prem Chand Gupta said.

 New Delhi, Oct. 4: The appointments committee of the cabinet has, ex-post facto, cleared the name of Sushma Chawla for holding additional charge as chairperson and managing director of Indian Airlines with effect from June 11 this year.




